  "local_port": 41794,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some really good Korean spas in Minneapolis?",
  "response": "Minneapolis offers several excellent Korean spas (jjimjilbangs) where you can enjoy a variety of relaxing and rejuvenating treatments. Here are some highly recommended options:\n\n### 1. **Central Wellness Spa**\n**Address:** 1827 Broadway Ave S #401, Minneapolis, MN 55407  \n**Website:** [centralwellspring.com](https://centralwellspring.com/)  \n**Highlights:**\n- Traditional Korean sauna facilities with multiple themed sauna rooms.\n- Hot and cold baths, including mineral and herbal pools.\n- Massage and body treatment services.\n- Relaxation areas with amenities like snacks and beverages.\n\n### 2. **BanSpa Korean Wellness Center**\n**Address:** 4101 Nicollet Ave S #840, Minneapolis, MN 55419  \n**Website:** [banspa.com](http://banspa.com/)  \n**Highlights:**\n- Spacious facilities offering various sauna rooms, including salt, jade, and ice rooms.\n- Comprehensive wellness services including body scrubs, massages, and facials.\n- Comfortable lounge areas with refreshments.\n- Hourly and membership pricing options.\n\n### 3. **Spa Supreme Korean Hot Pot Sauna**\n**Address:** 7900 York Ave N, Bloomington, MN 55431  \n**Website:** [spasupreme.com](http://spasupreme.com/)  \n**Highlights:**\n- Extensive range of saunas with different themes and temperatures.\n- Hot pot dining experience with a variety of broths and ingredients.\n- Private relaxation rooms and communal lounging areas.\n- Additional services like nail care and skincare treatments.\n\n### 4. **Palace Korean Spa**\n**Address:** 1234 University Ave N, Minneapolis, MN 55411  \n**Website:** [palacekoreanspa.com](http://palacekoreanspa.com/)  \n**Highlights:**\n- Authentic Korean spa experience with traditional design and amenities.\n- Multiple sauna rooms with unique features such as charcoal and cedar.\n- Health-focused treatments including acupuncture and herbal remedies.\n- On-site restaurant offering Korean cuisine.\n\n### 5. **Harmony Spa**\n**Address:** 5678 14th Ave S, Minneapolis, MN 55407  \n**Website:** [harmonyspa.com](http://harmonyspa.com/)  \n**Highlights:**\n- Modern spa facilities combining Korean traditions with contemporary wellness practices.\n- Variety of sauna types, including infrared and steam saunas.\n- Comprehensive menu of massages, facials, and body treatments.\n- Relaxing lounge areas with complimentary tea and snacks.\n\n### Tips for Visiting Korean Spas:\n- **Dress Code:** Many Korean spas require guests to wear provided uniforms or specific attire, especially in communal areas.\n- **Etiquette:** Maintain a quiet and respectful demeanor, as these spaces are meant for relaxation and tranquility.\n- **Hydration:** Drink plenty of water before and after your spa experience to stay hydrated.\n- **Reservations:** Some popular spas may require reservations, especially during peak hours or weekends.\n\nVisiting a Korean spa in Minneapolis can be a wonderful way to unwind, experience Korean wellness traditions, and enjoy quality time for self-care. Be sure to check each spa's website or contact them directly for the latest information on services, hours, and pricing.",
